{"id":161,"parent_id":160,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":161,"title":"Titus 1-3: \"Sound in the Faith\"","subtitle":"","short_title":"Titus 1-3: \"Sound in the Faith\"","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-to-titus/titus-1-3-sound-in-the-faith","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-to-titus/titus-1-3-sound-in-the-faith"},[".heading",{"id":"head2","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-to-titus/titus-1-3-sound-in-the-faith.head2"},["h1","Titus 1–3"],[".subtitle","“Sound in the Faith”"],[".intro","Many of the members in Crete were sinning and teaching incorrect principles. To help them become sound in the faith, Paul counseled Titus, their bishop, to “rebuke them sharply” (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/titus/1.13"},"Titus 1:13"],") and teach them sound doctrine (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/titus/2.1"},"Titus 2:1"],"). As you read this epistle to Titus, look for the doctrines Paul told him to teach to the Saints. How does knowing these truths make a difference in your life."]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-to-titus/titus-1-3-sound-in-the-faith.f1"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/titus/1"},"Titus 1"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Wanting"],"(v. 5)"],["td","Lacking"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","No striker"],"(v. 7)"],["td","Not a contentious person"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Circumcision"],"(v. 10)"],["td","Jewish Christians who still lived according to certain parts of the law of Moses"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Subvert"],"(v. 11)"],["td","Destroy, corrupt"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Rebuke"],"(v. 13)"],["td","Correct, admonish"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Abominable"],"(v. 16)"],["td",