9","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-to-titus/titus-1-3-sound-in-the-faith.p19"},"“True doctrine, understood, changes attitudes and behavior."],["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-to-titus/titus-1-3-sound-in-the-faith.p20"},"“The study of the doctrines of the gospel will improve behavior quicker than a study of behavior will improve behavior” (in Conference Report, Oct. 1986, 20; or",["span.emphasis","Ensign,"],"Nov. 1986, 17)."],[".figure",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-to-titus/titus-1-3-sound-in-the-faith.f5"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","Read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/titus/1.9,13"},"Titus 1:9, 13"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/titus/2.1,15"},"2:1, 15"],"; and 3:8. How can Elder Packer’s statement apply to Paul’s counsel to Titus?"]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","Read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/titus/2"},"Titus 2"],"to either a grandparent or a parent, then ask why this is good counsel for someone his or her age. Record the response in your notebook."]]]]]]],[".resources"]]]],"refs":null}
